@startuml 01-context
title Forge — Diagrama de Contexto (C4 Nível 1)

skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 15
}
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Usuário\n(solicitante)" as User
actor "Operador\n(dono do terminal)" as Ops

rectangle "Telegram" as TG #LightBlue {
  component "Bot do canal\n(BotFather token)" as Bot
}

rectangle "Forge" as Forge #LightYellow {
  component "Claude Code\n+ plugin Forge" as CC
  component "Servidor MCP\n(server.ts / Bun)" as MCP
  database "Estado do canal\n~/.claude/channels/<nome>/" as State
}

rectangle "Repositório local\n(working dir)" as Repo #LightGreen

User --> Bot : envia tarefa / pergunta\n(texto, foto, documento)
Bot <--> MCP : long polling (grammy)\nsendMessage / setReaction
MCP --> CC : notifications/claude/channel\n(MCP stdio)
CC --> MCP : forge_reply / forge_react /\nforge_edit_message /\nforge_download_attachment
MCP --> State : lê .env, access.json, mode,\npid, approved/, inbox/
CC --> Repo : lê/escreve código,\ncommits via git
Ops --> CC : `forge <canal>` (launcher shell)
Ops --> State : /forge:access, /forge:configure\n(aprovações, políticas)

note right of MCP
  Um servidor por canal.
  Resolve FORGE_CHANNEL →
  diretório de estado.
  Gating antes de notificar
  o Claude.
end note

note bottom of CC
  Spawna 4 subagentes em sequência
  para tarefas de desenvolvimento:
  PO → Tech Lead → Developer → QA.
end note

@enduml
